item.title: Trump team gets evidence early in Mar-a-Lago docs case
item.description: Tonight on The Last Word: Donald Trump begs Congress to intervene in the classified documents case after the special counsel hands over evidence. Also, a Trump campaign official testifies to the January 6 grand jury. Plus, Justice Alito faces scrutiny over his trip with a GOP donor. And Rep. George Santos’ father and aunt backed his $500K bail. Harry Litman, Bradley Moss, Ryan Reilly, Sen. Sheldon Whitehouse and Rep. Robert Garcia join Jonathan Capehart. Feed: https://podcastfeeds.nbcnews.com/lastword
